declarations.description:
`<yp-form>` is a wrapper around the HTML `<form>` element, that can
validate and submit both custom and native HTML elements. Note that this
is a breaking change from yp-form 1.0, which was a type extension.
declarations.name: YpForm

members.name: headers
members.description:
HTTP request headers to send. See PolymerElements/iron-ajax for
more details. Only works when `allowRedirect` is false.

members.name: saveResetValues
members.description:
Saves the values of all form elements that will be used when resetting
the form. Initially called asynchronously on attach. Any time you
call this function, the previously saved values for a form element will
be overwritten.

This function is useful if you are dynamically adding elements to
the form, or if your elements are asynchronously setting their values.

members.name: validate
members.description: Validates all the required elements (custom and native) in the form.

members.name: submit
members.description: Submits the form.

members.name: reset
members.description: Resets the form to the default values.

members.name: serializeForm
members.description:
Serializes the form as will be used in submission. Note that `serialize`
is a Polymer reserved keyword, so calling `someIronForm`.serialize()`
will give you unexpected results.

members.name: _isSubmittable
members.description:
An element is submittable if it is not disabled, and if it has a
'name' attribute. If we ignore the name, check if is validatable.
This allows `_findElements` to decide if to explore an element's shadowRoot
or not: an element implementing `validate()` is considered validatable, and
we don't search for validatables in its shadowRoot.

declarations.description: `yp-image` is an element for displaying an image that provides useful sizing and preloading options not found on the standard `` tag. The `sizing` option allows the image to be either cropped (`cover`) or letterboxed (`contain`) to fill a fixed user-size placed on the element. The `preload` option prevents the browser from rendering the image until the image is fully loaded. In the interim, either the element's CSS `background-color` can be be used as the placeholder, or the `placeholder` property can be set to a URL (preferably a data-URI, for instant rendering) for an placeholder image. The `fade` option (only valid when `preload` is set) will cause the placeholder image/color to be faded out once the image is rendered. Examples: Basically identical to `` tag: Will letterbox the image to fit: Will crop the image to fit: Will show light-gray background until the image loads: Will show a base-64 encoded placeholder image until the image loads: Will fade the light-gray background out once the image is loaded: Custom property | Description | Default ----------------|-------------|---------- `--yp-image-placeholder` | Mixin applied to #placeholder | `{}` `--yp-image-width` | Sets the width of the wrapped image | `auto` `--yp-image-height` | Sets the height of the wrapped image | `auto`
declarations.name: YpImage

members.name: src
members.description: The URL of an image.

members.name: alt
members.description: A short text alternative for the image.

members.name: crossorigin
members.description:
CORS enabled images support:
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/CORS_enabled_image

members.name: preventLoad
members.description:
When true, the image is prevented from loading and any placeholder is
shown.  This may be useful when a binding to the src property is known to
be invalid, to prevent 404 requests.

members.name: sizing
members.description:
Sets a sizing option for the image.  Valid values are `contain` (full
aspect ratio of the image is contained within the element and
letterboxed) or `cover` (image is cropped in order to fully cover the
bounds of the element), or `null` (default: image takes natural size).

members.name: position
members.description:
When a sizing option is used (`cover` or `contain`), this determines
how the image is aligned within the element bounds.

members.name: preload
members.description:
When `true`, any change to the `src` property will cause the
`placeholder` image to be shown until the new image has loaded.

members.name: placeholder
members.description:
This image will be used as a background/placeholder until the src image
has loaded.  Use of a data-URI for placeholder is encouraged for instant
rendering.

members.name: fade
members.description:
When `preload` is true, setting `fade` to true will cause the image to
fade into place.

members.name: loaded
members.description: Read-only value that is true when the image is loaded.

members.name: loading
members.description:
Read-only value that tracks the loading state of the image when the
`preload` option is used.

members.name: error
members.description: Read-only value that indicates that the last set `src` failed to load.

members.name: width
members.description:
Can be used to set the width of image (e.g. via binding); size may also
be set via CSS.

members.name: height
members.description:
Can be used to set the height of image (e.g. via binding); size may also
be set via CSS.

declarations.name: createBrowserHistory
declarations.description:
Browser history stores the location in regular URLs. This is the standard for
most web apps, but it requires some configuration on the server to ensure you
serve the same app at multiple URLs.

declarations.name: createHashHistory
declarations.description:
Hash history stores the location in window.location.hash. This makes it ideal
for situations where you don't want to send the location to the server for
some reason, either because you do cannot configure it or the URL space is
reserved for something else.

declarations.name: createMemoryHistory
declarations.description:
Memory history stores the current location in memory. It is designed for use
in stateful non-browser environments like tests and React Native.

declarations.name: parsePath
declarations.description: Parses a string URL path into its separate pathname, search, and hash components.
